description:
Steady werkout at Lower Woodland. Werkout Wednesday will be another high volume, steady effort werkout that builds off of our werkout 2 weeks ago. The goal of the werkout is to build our endurance muscles and metabolism. The werkout will be 2-4x15 min steady with 2 min recovery. The goal of this run is to fatigue the body through volume rather than through a hard pace, and the hilly nature of the Lower Woodland loop is a good way to play around with climbs/descent/flat. This werkout is great for anyone looking to do 50k+ races particularly on runnable trail. This is a time based werkout meant for all ability levels.

Meetup: Lower Woodland Soccer Parking, 5000 West Green Lake Way N, Seattle, WA 98103

A group will leave for a warm up at 6:30, start drills + strides at 6:50, and werkout starts at 7am. The werkout will take place on the hilly loop in Lower Woodland

Werkout:
2 mi warm up
form drills + strides
15 min, 6-7 RPE, steady (half marathon-marathon pace)
2 min, recovery
15 min, 6-7 RPE
2 min, recovery
15 min, 6-7 RPE (optional)
2 min, recovery
15 min, 6-7 RPE (optional)
2 mi cooldown

Please RSVP if you plan on joining.
title: Werkout Wednesday üêÑ 2-4x15 min steady

welcome to this week‚Äôs womxn run the herd event! we are headed to madrona for our monthly field trip to enjoy some madison park miles ‚Äî here‚Äôs what you can expect:

exact address for the event, carpooling, and the potluck sign up spreadsheet can be found on the #womxnruntheherd slack channel!! please come prepared with a headlamp, extra warm/dry layers, and some girl dinner to share!

*this event is open to women, trans, and non-binary people who are comfortable in a space that centers the experiences of women. our only rule is that nobody runs alone :) 

(we will be back to our regular routine of 6pm @ the brooks trailhead on monday, december 2nd)
